===古生代===
[[File:PIA02405.jpg|thumb]]
地球[[臭氧層|臭氧層]]形成后，其吸收了大部份太陽照射至地球的紫外線。其使得單細胞的有機物在著陸後的死亡機會大降，而[[原核生物|原核生物]]則能更佳地在沒有水份的環境裡複製與存活。原核生物大約在26億年前殖民陸地<ref name="pisani">{{cite journal en
 | last = Pisani | first = Davide | coauthors = Laura L. Poling, Maureen Lyons-Weiler, & S. Blair Hedges | date = 2004-01-19
 | title = The colonization of land by animals: molecular phylogeny and divergence times among arthropods |trans_title=動物殖民陸地：節肢動物的分子層面的種族發生與分離 | journal = BMC Biology
 | volume = 2 | issue = 1 | doi = 10.1186/1741-7007-2-1 | url = http://www.pubmedcentral.nih.gov/articlerender.fcgi?artid=333434#B17
}}</ref>（此條目假設的時鐘上午10時17分），這比[[真核生物|真核生物]]起源的時間更早。在一段很長的時間裡，陸地上只有極少量的多細胞有機體。超級大陸[[潘諾西亞大陸|潘諾西亞大陸]]在大約是假設時鐘的下午8時50分形成至9時5分分裂<ref name="liebermean">{{cite journal en | last = Lieberman | first = Bruce S. | year = 2003 | title = Taking the Pulse of the Cambrian Radiation | journal = Integrative and Comparative Biology | trans_title = 綜合與比較生物學 | volume = 43 | issue = 1 | pages = 229–237 | doi = 10.1093/icb/43.1.229 | url = http://icb.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/43/1/229 | access-date = 2006-05-28 | archive-date = 2006-02-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060209085805/http://icb.oxfordjournals.org/cgi/content/full/43/1/229 | dead-url = no }}</ref>（大約6億年前至5000萬年後）。而最早的[[脊椎動物|脊椎動物]]則在大約5億2000萬年前出現在海洋上<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-354">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life | url = https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0 |trans_title=物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖 | year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/354 354] | chapter = Lampreys and Hagfish
}}</ref>（此條目假設的時鐘的下午9時10分）。一個主要的[[寒武紀-奧陶紀滅絕事件|滅絕事件]]在[[寒武紀|寒武紀]]末期發生<ref name="bbc-cambrian">{{cite web en | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/cambrian.htm | title = The Mass Extinctions: The Late Cambrian Extinction | trans_title = 大量滅絕：寒武紀末期的滅絕 | publisher = [[BBC|BBC]] | accessdate = 2006-04-09 | archive-date = 2006-06-30 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060630061229/http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/cambrian.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>，而這滅絕事件在大約4億8500萬年前停止<ref name="landing">{{cite journal en | last = Landing | first = E. | coauthors = S. A. Bowring, K. L. Davidek, [[Richard_Fortey|R. A. Fortey]], & W. A. P. Wimbledon | year = 2000 | title = Cambrian–Ordovician boundary age and duration of the lowest Ordovician Tremadoc Series based on U–Pb zircon dates from Avalonian Wales | trans_title = 寒武紀 - 奧陶紀交替的歲月與基於Avalonian Wales的U–Pb鋯石測年法所得的持續的奧陶紀特馬豆克統 | journal = Geological Magazine | volume = 137 | issue = 5 | pages = 485–494 | doi = 10.1017/S0016756800004507 | url = http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=60617 | access-date = 2006-05-28 | archive-date = 2007-11-14 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071114232538/http://journals.cambridge.org/action/displayAbstract?fromPage=online&aid=60617 | dead-url = no }} (abstract)</ref>（此條目假設的時鐘的下午9時25分）。

數億年前，植物（可能是[[藻類|藻類]]）與[[真菌|真菌]]開始在水與陸地的邊緣，並於其後離開水域而生存。<ref name="Fortey-138">{{cite book en
 | last = Fortey | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Fortey
 | title = Life: A Natural History of the First Four Billion Years of Life on Earth |trans_title=生命：地球上生命頭四十億年的自然歷史
 | origyear = 1997 | publisher = Vintage Books | location = New York | id = ISBN 978-0-375-70261-7 | pages = 138–140 | chapter = Landwards
|date=September 1999}}</ref>經測定最古老的陸地真菌與植物的化石後，得知其該在大約在4億8000萬年至4億6000萬年前生存（此條目假設的時鐘的下午9時28分至9時34分），雖然分子的證據顯示真菌可能早於十億年前（此條目假設的時鐘的下午6時40分）已殖民陸地；而植物早於七億年前已殖民陸地（此條目假設的時鐘的下午8時20分）。<ref name="heckman">{{cite journal en
 | last = Heckman | first = D. S. | coauthors = D. M. Geiser, B. R. Eidell, R. L. Stauffer, N. L. Kardos, & S. B. Hedges
 | date= August 10, 2001 | title = Molecular evidence for the early colonization of land by fungi and plants. |trans_title=早期真菌與植物殖民陸地的分子的支持證據。
 | journal = [[科学_(期刊)|Science]] | volume = 10 | issue = 293 | pages = 1129–1133
 | id = PMID 11498589 |doi=10.1126/science.1061457 | url = http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/query.fcgi?cmd=Retrieve&db=PubMed&dopt=Abstract&list_uids=11498589
}} (abstract)</ref>剛開始時仍是在水域邊緣存活，但是在此新環境裡的持續殖民使得突變與變化開始出現。而首隻離開海洋的動物的時間則並不準備地得知，所知的最明確、最古老的證據指出[[節肢動物|節肢動物]]大約在4億5000萬年前在陸地出現<ref name="johnson">{{cite journal en | last = Johnson | first = E. W. | coauthors = D. E. G. Briggs, R. J. Suthren, J. L. Wright, & S. P. Tunniclifff | title = Non-marine arthropod traces from the subaereal Ordivician Borrowdale volcanic group, English Lake District | trans_title = 在subaereal Ordivician Borrowdale的火山群追踪陸上的節肢動物，英國湖區 | journal = Geological Magazine | volume = 131 | issue = 3 | pages = 395–406 | url = http://geolmag.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/131/3/395 | date = May 1994 | access-date = 2006-05-28 | archive-date = 2006-06-28 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060628162313/http://geolmag.geoscienceworld.org/cgi/content/abstract/131/3/395 | dead-url = no }} (abstract)</ref>（此條目假設的時鐘的下午9時40分），其能在陸地繁盛與更佳地適應的原因可能是陸地上的植物提供了大量的食物來源。而亦有一些不能確定的證據指出節肢動物可能早於5億3000萬年前就已在陸地上出現。<ref name="macnaughton">{{cite journal en | last = MacNaughton | first = Robert B. | coauthors = Jennifer M. Cole, Robert W. Dalrymple, Simon J. Braddy, Derek E. G. Briggs, & Terrence D. Lukie | year = 2002 | title = First steps on land: Arthropod trackways in Cambrian-Ordovician eolian sandstone, southeastern Ontario, Canada | trans_title = 陸地上的首步：節肢動物在寒武紀 - 奧陶紀活動足跡，加拿大南安大略 | journal = Geology | volume = 30 | issue = 5 | pages = 391–394 | doi = 10.1130/0091-7613(2002)030<0391:FSOLAT>2.0.CO;2 | url = http://www.gsajournals.org/gsaonline/?request=get-abstract&issn=0091-7613&volume=30&page=391 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20120427083839/http://www.gsajournals.org/gsaonline/?request=get-abstract&issn=0091-7613&volume=30&page=391 | archivedate = 2012-04-27 | access-date = 2006-05-28 }} (abstract)</ref>在[[奥陶纪|奧陶紀]]末前，即4億4400萬年前（此條目假設的時鐘的下午9時40分），另一次[[奧陶紀－志留紀滅絕事件|滅絕事件]]發生，可能是與其同時的[[冰河時期|冰河時期]]所造成的結果。<ref name="bbc-ordovician">{{cite web en | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/ordovician.htm | title = The Mass Extinctions: The Late Ordovician Extinction | trans_title = 大量滅絕：奧陶紀末期的滅絕 | publisher = [[BBC|BBC]] | accessdate = 2006-05-22 | archive-date = 2006-02-21 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060221134019/http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/ordovician.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>

大約在3億8000萬年至3億7500百萬前（此條目假設的下午10時），[[四足動物|四足動物]]由魚類進化而成。<ref name="clack-sa">{{cite journal en | last = Clack | first = Jennifer A. | title = Getting a Leg Up on Land | trans_title = 陸地上四足動物的出現 | journal = [[Scientific_American|Scientific American]] | url = http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000DC8B8-EA15-137C-AA1583414B7F0000&sc=I100322 | date = December 2005 | access-date = 2006-05-28 | archive-date = 2007-10-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20071010051658/http://www.sciam.com/article.cfm?articleID=000DC8B8-EA15-137C-AA1583414B7F0000&sc=I100322 | dead-url = no }}</ref>人們估計因為鱼鳍進化為四肢使得首個四足動物可以使其頭部離開水域並呼吸[[空氣|空氣]]。這使其可以在缺氧的水域裡生存或在淺水區追捕獵物。<ref name="clack-sa" />其可能在其後的一段歲月裡在陸地進行冒險。其最後有部份可能變得十分適應陸地生活並在成年時在陸地上生活，雖然其在水裡孵化並在水裡生蛋，以上便是四足動物的起源。在大約3億6500萬年前（此條目假的時鐘的下午10時4分），另一個[[泥盆紀後期滅絕事件|滅絕事件]]出現發生，這可能是因為全球冷化的結果。<ref name="bbc-devonian">{{cite web en | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/devonian.htm | title = The Mass Extinctions: The Late Devonian Extinction | trans_title = 大滅絕：泥盆紀的末期大滅絕 | publisher = [[BBC|BBC]] | accessdate = 2006-04-04 | archive-date = 1999-10-09 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/19991009225255/http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/devonian.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>大約在3億6000萬年前（此條目假設的時鐘的下午10時），植物開始包含[[種子|種子]]，使其在陸地上繁衍的速度大增。<ref name="willis">{{cite book en
 | last = Willis | first = K. J. | coauthors = J. C. McElwain | title = The Evolution of Plants (植物的進化)| year = 2002
 | publisher = Oxford University Press | location = Oxford | id = ISBN 978-0-19-850065-0 | pages = 93
}}</ref><ref name="waikato">{{cite web | url = http://sci.waikato.ac.nz/evolution/plantEvolution.shtml | title = Plant Evolution (植物的進化) | publisher = [[University_of_Waikato|University of Waikato]] | accessdate = 2006-04-07 | archive-date = 2012-08-08 | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/69kxl1qxp?url=http://sci.waikato.ac.nz/evolution/plantEvolution.shtml | dead-url = yes }}</ref>

大約在2000萬年後（3億4000萬年前<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-293">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =[[The_Ancestor’s_Tale:_A_Pilgrimage_to_the_Dawn_of_Life|The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life]]（物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖）| year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/293 293]–296 | chapter = Amphibians
}}</ref>，此條目假設的時鐘的下午10時12分），[[羊膜卵|羊膜卵]]的進化使得蛋可以在陸地上誕下，這是四足動物胚胎的生存優勢。這使得[[羊膜動物|羊膜動物]]由基干四足動物分離出來。再經過3000萬年後（3億1000萬年前<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-254">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =[[The_Ancestor’s_Tale:_A_Pilgrimage_to_the_Dawn_of_Life|The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life]]（物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖）| year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/254 254]–256 | chapter = Sauropsids
}}</ref>，此條目假設的時鐘的下午10時22分），由[[爬行動物|蜥形類]]（包含了[[鳥類|鳥類]]與非鳥類、非哺乳類[[爬行動物|爬行動物]]）裡分離出[[合弓綱|合弓綱]]（包含了[[哺乳動物|哺乳動物]]）。

===中生代===
[[File:Extinction_Intensity(in_Chinese).jpg|thumb]]
3億年前（此條目假設的時鐘下午10時25分），最近期的超級大陸[[盤古大陸|盤古大陸]]形成。在2億5100萬年前（此條目假設的時鐘下午10時40分）發生了地球历史上最嚴峻的[[二疊紀-三疊紀滅絕事件|二疊紀-三疊紀滅絕事件]]<ref name="bbc-permian-triassic">{{cite web en
 | year = 2002
 | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/science/horizon/2002/dayearthdied.shtml
 | title = The Day the Earth Nearly Died (地球幾乎死亡的日子)
 | work = Horizon
 | publisher = [[BBC|BBC]]
 | accessdate = 2006-04-09
 | archive-date = 2012-08-08
 | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/69kxduqIE?url=http://www.bbc.co.uk/science/horizon/2002/dayearthdied.shtml
 | dead-url = no
 }}</ref>，當時[[地球|地球]]上70%的陸生[[脊椎動物|脊椎動物]]，以及高達96%的海中生物消失<ref name="Benton">{{en}}{{cite book|author=Benton M J|date=2005|title=When Life Nearly Died: The Greatest Mass Extinction of All Time|publisher=Thames & Hudson|isbn=978-0500285732}}</ref>；這次滅絕事件也造成[[昆蟲|昆蟲]]的唯一一次大量滅絕。這可能是[[西伯利亞暗色岩|西伯利亞暗色岩]]（Siberian Traps）的火山不斷爆發的影響。但生命仍未完全滅絕，有小部份生命繼續生存，在大約2億3300萬年前<ref name="bbc-new blood">{{cite episode | title = New Blood | episodelink =  | series = Walking with Dinosaurs（與恐龍同行） | serieslink = 与恐龙同行 | airdate = 1999 | publisher = [[BBC|BBC]] | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/sn/prehistoric_life/dinosaurs/chronology/220mya1.shtml | access-date = 2006-05-28 | archive-date = 2005-12-12 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20051212114953/http://www.bbc.co.uk/sn/prehistoric_life/dinosaurs/chronology/220mya1.shtml | dead-url = no }}</ref>（此條目假設的時鐘的下午10時47分），[[恐龍|恐龍]]由其爬蟲類祖先分離出來。大部份恐龍成功在二億年前（此條目假設的時鐘的下午10時56分）的[[三疊紀-侏羅紀滅絕事件|三疊紀-侏羅紀滅絕事件]]裡存活下來<ref name="bbc-triassic">{{cite web en | url = http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/triassic.htm | title = The Mass Extinctions: The Late Triassic Extinction | trans_title = 大滅絕：三疊紀末期大滅絕 | publisher = [[BBC|BBC]] | accessdate = 2006-04-09 | archive-date = 2006-08-13 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060813230832/http://www.bbc.co.uk/education/darwin/exfiles/triassic.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>，而其很快便成為脊椎動物裡的霸主。雖然在此時期有部份的哺乳類動物分離出來，存在的哺乳類全都是細小的動物如[[鼩鼱|鼩鼱]]。<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-169">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life | url = https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0 |trans_title=物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖 | year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
