}}</ref>

==人類的出现==

{{main|人類演化}}

在600萬年前（此條目假設的時鐘的下午11時58分），少量生存在非洲的類猿人為現代人類與其親戚[[黑猩猩|黑猩猩]]的最後共同祖先。<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-100">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =[[The_Ancestor’s_Tale:_A_Pilgrimage_to_the_Dawn_of_Life|The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life]]（物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖）| year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/100 100]–101 | chapter = Chimpanzees
}}</ref>其家族只有兩個分支仍然存活。在其家族分離後不久，因為某些仍在爭論的原因，類猿人的一支發展出了[[兩足動物|站立步行]]的能力。<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-95">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =[[The_Ancestor’s_Tale:_A_Pilgrimage_to_the_Dawn_of_Life|The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life]]（物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖）| year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/95 95]–99 | chapter = Ape-Men
}}</ref>其[[腦|腦]]部迅速地變大，而在大約200萬年前（此條目假設的時鐘下午11時59分22秒，或午夜前38秒），[[人屬|人屬]]裡的首個動物出現。<ref name="Fortey-300">{{cite book en
 | last = Fortey | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Fortey
 | title = Life: A Natural History of the First Four Billion Years of Life on Earth (生命：地球上生命頭四十億年的自然歷史),
 | origyear = 1997 | publisher = Vintage Books | location = New York | id = ISBN 978-0-375-70261-7 | pages = 38 | chapter = Humanity
|date=September 1999}}</ref>每一代有機生物的種類，甚至是屬皆可能有所不同。在大約相同時間，另一支分支則分裂為[[普通黑猩猩|普通黑猩猩]]（common chimpanzee）的祖先與[[倭黑猩猩|倭黑猩猩]]（bonobo）的祖先，這種進化仍不斷在所有生命裡進行。<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-100" />

[[直立人|直立人]]（''Homo erectus''）最晚在79萬年前掌握了控制[[火|火]]的能力<ref name="goren-inbar">{{cite journal en | last = Goren-Inbar | first = Naama | coauthors = Nira Alperson, Mordechai E. Kislev, Orit Simchoni, Yoel Melamed, Adi Ben-Nun, & Ella Werker | date = 2004-04-30 | title = Evidence of Hominin Control of Fire at Gesher Benot Ya`aqov, Israel (在以色列Gesher Benot Ya`aqov所得到的人類控制火的證據) | journal = [[科学_(期刊)|Science]] | volume = 304 | issue = 5671 | pages = 725–727 | doi = 10.1126/science.1095443 | url = http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/304/5671/725 | accessdate = 2006-04-11 | archive-date = 2006-03-10 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060310220348/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/abstract/304/5671/725 | dead-url = no }} <small>(abstract)</small></ref>，但可能早於150萬年前已經掌握了<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-67">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =[[The_Ancestor’s_Tale:_A_Pilgrimage_to_the_Dawn_of_Life|The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life]]（物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖）| year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/67 67] | chapter = Ergasts
}}</ref>（此條目假設的時鐘的最終28秒至15秒）。對於[[語言起源|語言起源]]的考究更為困難；因為難以得知直立人（''Homo erectus''）是否已能說話，還是直至[[智人|智人]]（''Homo sapiens''）時才被有說話的能力。<ref name="Dawkins-Ancestors-67-71">{{cite book en
 | last = Dawkins | first = Richard | authorlink = Richard Dawkins
 | title =[[The_Ancestor’s_Tale:_A_Pilgrimage_to_the_Dawn_of_Life|The Ancestor’s Tale: A Pilgrimage to the Dawn of Life]]（物種原型的故事：生命黎明的朝聖）| year = 2004
 | publisher = Houghton Mifflin Company | location = Boston | id = ISBN 978-0-618-00583-3
 | pages = [https://archive.org/details/ancestorstale00rich_0/page/67 67]–71 | chapter = Ergasts
}}</ref>隨著腦的體積增大，嬰兒生產的速度增快，在其頭部成長得大於[[骨盆|骨盆]]前便要出生。因此其適應力較高，並擁有更高的學習容量，但依賴他人的時間也為之加長。社交技巧變得更為複雜，語言變得更為先進，而工具變得更為精細。這為長遠的合作與腦部發展作出了貢獻。<ref name="McNeill-7">{{cite book en
 | last = McNeill | first = Willam H. | authorlink = William McNeill
 | title = A World History (世界歷史)| origyear = 1967 | edition = 4th ed. | year = 1999
 | publisher = Oxford University Press | location = New York | id = ISBN 978-0-19-511615-1
 | pages = 7 | chapter = In The Beginning 
}}</ref>

解剖學上的現代人類「智人」相信是在20萬年前（此條目假設的時鐘的最終2秒）或更早時期於[[單起源說|非洲]]某處誕生；最古老的智人化石可追溯至16萬年前。<ref name="gibbons">{{cite journal en | last = Gibbons | first = Ann | date = 2003-06-13 | title = Oldest Members of ''Homo sapiens'' Discovered in Africa (最早的''智人''於非洲發現) | journal = [[科学_(期刊)|Science]] | volume = 300 | issue = 5626 | pages = 1641 | doi = 10.1126/science.300.5626.1641 | url = http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/summary/300/5626/1641 | accessdate = 2006-04-11 | archive-date = 2006-03-06 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20060306123415/http://www.sciencemag.org/cgi/content/summary/300/5626/1641 | dead-url = no }} (abstract)</ref>首個有證據顯示擁有[[精神活動|精神活動]]的人類為[[尼安德塔人|尼安德塔人]]（Neanderthal，通常被歸類為沒有後代的獨立分類）；其會在別人死後埋葬其屍身，通常亦會以食物或工具作陪葬物。<ref name="hopfe">{{cite book en
 | last = Hopfe  | first = Lewis M. | title = Religions of the World | origyear = 1976 | edition = 4th ed. | id = ISBN 978-0-02-356930-2
 | year = 1987 | publisher = MacMillan Publishing Company | location = New York | pages = 17 | chapter = Characteristics of Basic Religions（基本信仰的特徵）
}}</ref>然而，擁有更複雜的信念的人類的證據，如早期[[克羅馬儂人|克羅馬儂人]]（Cro-Magnon）的[[洞穴壁畫|洞穴壁畫]]（可能有著魔幻或信仰的重要性）<ref name="hopfe-19">{{cite book en
 | last = Hopfe  | first = Lewis M. | title = Religions of the World (世界信仰)| origyear = 1976 | edition = 4th ed. | id = ISBN 978-0-02-356930-2
 | year = 1987 | publisher = MacMillan Publishing Company | location = New York | pages = 17–19 | chapter = Characteristics of Basic Religions
}}</ref>直至32000年前（此條目假設的時鐘的最終0.6秒）才出現。<ref>{{cite web en | url = http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/chav/hd_chav.htm | title = Chauvet Cave (沙夫特洞穴) | publisher = [[Metropolitan_Museum_of_Art|Metropolitan Museum of Art]] | accessdate = 2006-04-11 | archive-date = 2012-08-08 | archive-url = https://www.webcitation.org/69kxeSQXK?url=http://www.metmuseum.org/toah/hd/chav/hd_chav.htm | dead-url = no }}</ref>克羅馬農人亦有著石製小雕像如[[維倫多夫維納斯|維倫多夫維納斯]]（Venus of Willendorf），可能亦有著信仰的含義。<ref name="hopfe-19" />在11000年前（此條目假設的時鐘的最終0.2秒），部份「智人」抵達了[[南美洲|南美洲]]的南端，最晚有人居住的大陸。<ref name="oxford-atlas">{{cite book en
 | editor = Patrick K. O’Brien, ed. | title = Atlas of World History (世界歷史地圖集)| origyear = 2002 | edition = concise edition
 | year = 2003 | publisher = [[Oxford_University_Press|Oxford University Press]] | location = New York | id = ISBN 978-0-19-521921-0 | pages = 16 | chapter = The Human Revolution
}}</ref>這時人類使用的工具與語言繼續在改進；而人際關係亦變得更為複雜。

